---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { SITE } from '../../../data/site';

const title = 'Salado Metal Roof Installation | Red Roan Construction';
const description = 'Standing seam Galvalume steel roof on a 1970s Hill Country ranch home in Salado TX. 2,800 sq ft. 40-year material warranty. Energy bills down ~15% first summer.';

const schema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'Article',
  headline: title,
  description,
  author: { '@type': 'Organization', name: SITE.name },
  publisher: { '@type': 'Organization', name: SITE.name },
};
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description} schema={schema}>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="bg-brand-navy text-white py-16 md:py-20 relative overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-15">
      <img
        src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1591088398332-8a7791972843?w=1600&q=60&auto=format&fit=crop"
        alt=""
        class="w-full h-full object-cover"
      />
    </div>
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-r from-brand-navy via-brand-navy/90 to-transparent"></div>
    <div class="relative max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4">
      <nav class="flex items-center gap-2 text-white/50 text-sm mb-6">
        <a href="/" class="hover:text-white transition">Home</a>
        <span>/</span>
        <a href="/projects/" class="hover:text-white transition">Projects</a>
        <span>/</span>
        <span class="text-white/80">Salado Metal Roof Installation</span>
      </nav>
      <p class="text-brand-accent font-semibold text-sm tracking-widest uppercase mb-3">Metal Roofing · Standing Seam</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold leading-tight mb-4 max-w-2xl">
        Salado Metal Roof Installation
      </h1>
      <p class="text-white/70 text-lg max-w-xl mb-8">
        A Hill Country homeowner stopped patching and invested in a 40-year standing seam Galvalume roof. Three days. Done right.
      </p>
      <!-- Stats row -->
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-6">
        {[
          { label: 'Square Footage', value: '2,800 sq ft' },
          { label: 'Material', value: 'Galvalume Standing Seam' },
          { label: 'Gauge', value: '26-gauge steel' },
          { label: 'Duration', value: '3 days' },
          { label: 'Completed', value: 'January 2025' },
          { label: 'Expected Life', value: '40+ years' },
        ].map(stat => (
          <div class="bg-white/10 rounded-lg px-4 py-3 min-w-[120px]">
            <p class="text-white/50 text-xs uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">{stat.label}</p>
            <p class="text-white font-bold text-sm">{stat.value}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Main content -->
  <article class="bg-brand-light">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-14 md:py-20">

      <!-- Hero image -->
      <div class="rounded-xl overflow-hidden shadow-md mb-12">
        <img
          src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1591088398332-8a7791972843?w=1200&q=80&auto=format&fit=crop"
          alt="Standing seam metal roof installation on Hill Country ranch home, Salado TX"
          class="w-full h-80 md:h-[480px] object-cover"
          loading="eager"
        />
      </div>

      <!-- Problem narrative -->
      <section class="mb-12">
        <p class="text-brand-accent font-semibold text-sm tracking-widest uppercase mb-3">The Situation</p>
        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-extrabold text-brand-navy mb-6">Third repair in five years. She was done patching.</h2>

        <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-slate-600 space-y-5">
          <p>
            Sandra had owned the Salado ranch house for eleven years. The original asphalt shingle roof was already aging when she bought it, and by 2024 she was on her third repair call. The first was a valley leak after a heavy spring storm. The second was a blown-off section of shingles after a straight-line wind event. The third was a slow drip near the chimney flashing that turned out to be two separate issues compounding each other.
          </p>
          <p>
            She wasn't angry — she'd gotten decent service from previous contractors — but she was tired of calling. Every repair bought another year or two at best, and she was watching the cumulative cost creep toward the price of a full replacement anyway. She called Red Roan in November 2024 and asked a direct question: would metal make sense for her house, or was it marketing?
          </p>
          <p>
            We spent forty-five minutes with her going through the honest math. Her current shingle roof was at best five years from needing full replacement regardless of patches. A standing seam metal roof, installed correctly, would still be performing at the 40-year mark on a Hill Country home. The carrying cost per year — factoring in material price, installation, and zero maintenance — was significantly lower than cycling through asphalt roofs. She decided the same week.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Process photos row -->
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-3 gap-4 mb-12">
        <div class="rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
          <img
            src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1558618666-fcd25c85cd64?w=800&q=80&auto=format&fit=crop"
            alt="Existing shingles stripped before metal roof install"
            class="w-full h-52 object-cover hover:scale-105 transition duration-300"
            loading="lazy"
          />
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-400 mt-2 px-1">Day one: full tear-off — no overlay on a metal job</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
          <img
            src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1504307651254-35680f356dfd?w=800&q=80&auto=format&fit=crop"
            alt="Ice and water shield installed at eaves and valleys"
            class="w-full h-52 object-cover hover:scale-105 transition duration-300"
            loading="lazy"
          />
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-400 mt-2 px-1">Ice & water shield, insulation board, and clip track before panels</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
          <img
            src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1591088398332-8a7791972843?w=800&q=80&auto=format&fit=crop"
            alt="Completed Galvalume standing seam metal roof Salado TX"
            class="w-full h-52 object-cover hover:scale-105 transition duration-300"
            loading="lazy"
          />
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-400 mt-2 px-1">Finished — Galvalume natural metallic, standing seam panels locked</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Solution narrative -->
      <section class="mb-12">
        <p class="text-brand-accent font-semibold text-sm tracking-widest uppercase mb-3">What We Did</p>
        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-extrabold text-brand-navy mb-6">No overlay. Full installation. Three days.</h2>

        <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-slate-600 space-y-5">
          <p>
            We talked Sandra through the material choice before the contract was signed. Standing seam vs corrugated came down to two things: longevity of the seam geometry under Texas temperature cycling, and the Hill Country aesthetic. Standing seam panels expand and contract as a single floating system — the seam does not penetrate the panel, so there is no fastener exposure for water to work through over time. It is also a cleaner, more architectural look on a ranch-style home.
          </p>
          <p>
            For the material, we selected Galvalume steel in the natural metallic finish. Galvalume is an aluminum-zinc coated steel that handles the temperature extremes in Central Texas better than painted panels over the long term. The natural finish reflects heat rather than absorbing it — which directly affects attic temperature and in turn cooling load. Sandra noticed a reduction in her energy bills by the following summer.
          </p>
          <p>
            Day one was full tear-off. We never overlay a metal job — the panels need a flat, sound deck and proper ventilation underneath. With the shingles off, we inspected every sheet of plywood and replaced three sections that had softened. Ice and water shield went across all eaves and both valleys. A continuous layer of 1.5-inch polyisocyanurate foam board was installed over the whole deck before the clip track — this adds an R-6 thermal break between the metal and the living space, reducing condensation and adding meaningful insulation value. Days two and three were panel installation, trim, and flashing — ridge, rakes, and all penetrations sealed with matching trim stock.
          </p>
          <p>
            Sandra called us about six months after the job was done to say her first full summer with the metal roof had come in about 15% lower on her electricity bill compared to the prior year. That is in line with what a properly installed reflective metal roof does in Texas heat.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Specs box + Outcome side by side -->
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 mb-12">

        <!-- Specs -->
        <div class="bg-white border border-slate-200 rounded-xl p-8 shadow-sm">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-brand-navy mb-6 flex items-center gap-2">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-brand-accent" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
              <path d="M9 5H7a2 2 0 00-2 2v12a2 2 0 002 2h10a2 2 0 002-2V7a2 2 0 00-2-2h-2M9 5a2 2 0 002 2h2a2 2 0 002-2M9 5a2 2 0 012-2h2a2 2 0 012 2"/>
            </svg>
            Project Specs
          </h3>
          <dl class="space-y-4">
            {[
              { label: 'Location', value: 'Salado, TX' },
              { label: 'Completed', value: 'January 2025' },
              { label: 'Square Footage', value: '2,800 sq ft' },
              { label: 'Roof Type', value: 'Standing seam' },
              { label: 'Material', value: 'Galvalume steel — natural metallic' },
              { label: 'Gauge', value: '26-gauge' },
              { label: 'Insulation', value: '1.5" polyiso foam board (R-6)' },
              { label: 'Underlayment', value: 'Ice & water shield at eaves/valleys' },
              { label: 'Duration', value: '3 days' },
              { label: 'Material Warranty', value: '40 years' },
              { label: 'Workmanship Warranty', value: '5 years (Red Roan)' },
            ].map(item => (
              <div class="flex justify-between items-start gap-4 py-2 border-b border-slate-100 last:border-0">
                <dt class="text-slate-500 text-sm flex-shrink-0">{item.label}</dt>
                <dd class="text-brand-navy font-semibold text-sm text-right">{item.value}</dd>
              </div>
            ))}
          </dl>
        </div>

        <!-- Outcome block -->
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-6">
          <div class="bg-brand-navy text-white rounded-xl p-8">
            <h3 class="text-white font-bold text-base mb-4">The result, in her words</h3>
            <blockquote class="text-white/90 text-base leading-relaxed mb-4">
              "I got a metal roof installed and couldn't be happier. The price was fair, the workmanship is excellent, and they handled everything. No more repair calls."
            </blockquote>
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
              <div>
                <p class="font-bold text-white text-sm">Sandra K.</p>
                <p class="text-white/50 text-xs">Salado, TX</p>
              </div>
              <div class="flex gap-0.5 ml-auto">
                {[1,2,3,4,5].map(() => (
                  <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-brand-accent" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                    <path d="M9.049 2.927c.3-.921 1.603-.921 1.902 0l1.07 3.292a1 1 0 00.95.69h3.462c.969 0 1.371 1.24.588 1.81l-2.8 2.034a1 1 0 00-.364 1.118l1.07 3.292c.3.921-.755 1.688-1.54 1.118l-2.8-2.034a1 1 0 00-1.175 0l-2.8 2.034c-.784.57-1.838-.197-1.539-1.118l1.07-3.292a1 1 0 00-.364-1.118L2.98 8.72c-.783-.57-.38-1.81.588-1.81h3.461a1 1 0 00.951-.69l1.07-3.292z"/>
                  </svg>
                ))}
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-brand-warm rounded-xl p-6">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-brand-navy text-base mb-3">Why this job worked</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-slate-600 text-sm">
              {[
                'No overlay — clean deck means no hidden problems compounding over time',
                'Foam insulation board eliminates the condensation problem common in Texas metal roofs',
                'Galvalume outperforms painted panels over 40 years in high-UV climates',
                '~15% energy reduction in first summer from reflective surface + R-6 thermal break',
              ].map(point => (
                <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                  <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-brand-accent mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5">
                    <path d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/>
                  </svg>
                  {point}
                </li>
              ))}
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Related services -->
      <section class="border-t border-slate-200 pt-10 mb-10">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-brand-navy mb-5">Related Services</h3>
        <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
          {[
            { href: '/services/roof-replacement/', label: 'Roof Replacement', desc: 'Full metal and asphalt shingle replacement for residential and light commercial.' },
            { href: '/services/roof-inspection/', label: 'Free Roof Inspection', desc: 'Not sure if repair or replace is the right call? We will tell you honestly.' },
            { href: '/services/roof-repair/', label: 'Roof Repair', desc: 'If repair is the right answer, we do that too.' },
          ].map(s => (
            <a href={s.href} class="bg-white border border-slate-200 rounded-lg p-5 hover:border-brand-accent hover:shadow-sm transition group">
              <p class="font-semibold text-brand-navy text-sm group-hover:text-brand-accent transition mb-1">{s.label} →</p>
              <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm leading-snug">{s.desc}</p>
            </a>
          ))}
          <a href="/projects/" class="bg-white border border-slate-200 rounded-lg p-5 hover:border-brand-accent hover:shadow-sm transition group">
            <p class="font-semibold text-brand-navy text-sm group-hover:text-brand-accent transition mb-1">All Projects →</p>
            <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm leading-snug">Browse more completed roofing projects across Central Texas.</p>
          </a>
        </div>
      </section>

    </div>
  </article>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="bg-brand-navy py-16 text-center">
    <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-4">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-extrabold text-white mb-4">Thinking about going metal?</h2>
      <p class="text-white/70 mb-8">
        We will walk you through the honest math — whether metal makes sense for your home, what material is right for your climate, and what the real cost difference is over time.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
        <a href="/contact/" class="bg-brand-accent text-white px-8 py-3 rounded-lg font-semibold hover:opacity-90 transition">
          Get a Free Quote
        </a>
        <a href={`tel:${SITE.phones.hillCountryTel}`} class="border border-white/30 text-white px-8 py-3 rounded-lg font-semibold hover:bg-white/10 transition">
          Call {SITE.phones.hillCountry}
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
